<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[156,604,532,591]" box="[330,429,564,591]" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">
(
<figureCitation box="[338,421,564,591]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="15.[115,124,1635,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-29@16.[178,786,587,913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIG. 9. — Silicified plants from the Permian of Sardinia: A, Cordaixylon sp., transverse section of a partly decorticated small stem with a solid parenchymatous pith; on the left the closely associated rachis (P) with several xylem bundles may represent a petiole of the same plant (SAR24B4L13);B, Cordaites leaves associated with Pecopteris pinnules;the broadest leaf (CC) with interfascicular scleren-" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4607883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4607883/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,647,628,908]" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">
In this leaf the lamina is thin and of variable thickness: 
<quantity box="[170,255,659,686]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
between veins to 
<quantity box="[443,527,659,686]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
at the level of veins due to the presence of triangular hypodermal sclerotic strands above and below the bundle sheath. This results in a typical superficial ribbing characteristic of the species 
<taxonomicName box="[404,562,786,812]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cordaitaceae" genus="Cordaites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cordaitales" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuistriatus">
<emphasis box="[404,562,786,812]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">C. tenuistriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="RENAULT B." box="[217,383,818,845]" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" pagination="213 - 348" refId="ref13831" refString="RENAULT B. 1879. - Structure comparee de quelques tiges de la flore Carbonifere, Nouvelles Archives du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 2: 213 - 348." type="journal article" year="1879">Renault (1879)</bibRefCitation>
from the Pennsylvanian of Grand-Croix. The interval between veins is less than 
<quantity box="[169,258,881,908]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
, i.e. about 17 veins per cm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
